#: ../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:3 c44f36e3868647d28606c5049d2f1374
msgid "Usability & UX"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:5 1b334381ccde4f8c8d4b8c5fe72bb119
msgid ""
"Software that is too complicated to use, is often unused. Because we want as"
" many people as possible to benefit from its unique security properties, the"
" usability and user experience of Qubes OS is an utmost priority!"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:7 a0ba5e1703e8469aa336dfbf8d8f8f2b
msgid ""
"We ask anyone developing for Qubes OS to please read through this guide to "
"better understand the user experience we strive to achieve. We also ask them"
" to review `our visual style guide <https://www.qubes-os.org/doc/visual-"
"style-guide/>`__ for other design related information."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:12
#: abf0a772fedd4e0e99653c3ebb59bfca
msgid "Easy To Use"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:14
#: 1a91a39b5f8a4918b73bb16ffc890ee8
msgid ""
"An ideal user experience is friendly, and it beckons a new user to explore "
"the interface. In this process, they can naturally discover how to use the "
"software. Below are some guidelines that will help you design a user "
"interface that accomplishes this goal."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:16
#: 88b530a9c64d42d59d016ec66678e528
msgid "|redx| **Interfaces Should Not**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:245
#: c75d8d29813943fcac75d88e41547ff3 cd4cf41ad3be435e9e017d619b87e0ce
#: 8c1ada94a8d24fa6a3e46204ef18c5ac 5df087e205c84451b136f6610fa4602b
#: 2b8c2174f06a443381873e3752f60b56 fc894f4592d14e68bc7b26aa3b699d64
msgid "redx"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:18
#: 0282b807a8a24cd48a3f0c0dd2fd273e
msgid "Require extensive configuration before a user can *begin* doing things"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:20
#: 24dc97e659f343da89d4faf3e18511d9
msgid ""
"Make it possible to break provided features or actions in unrecoverable ways"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:22
#: bd4560b70c3742909ac97026fb6c0b2d
msgid "Perform actions which compromise security and data"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:24
#: 101683a92b734817987b24876d80fe07
msgid "Overwhelm the user with too much information and cognitive load"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:26
#: 1f2f48d8444e48d1ada68e76a07455f9
msgid ""
"Perhaps the most common cause of mistakes is complexity. If there is a "
"configuration setting that will significantly affect the user’s experience, "
"choose a safe and smart default then tuck this setting in an ``Advanced "
"Settings`` panel."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:28
#: 0c2b83360a3d4963aac0130609f82283
msgid "|checkmark| **Interfaces Should**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:244
#: f70a9c27780e479a82ffa5d4f6161f73 f2e34f8c75c74ac08a53b0ce3cd3695c
#: 7f445efd13ca43fbb879cefcc011fff6 e3c8b9e159d0462a93c1099946bd5a83
#: a0acc89168024738bdfa629f55b96bfb 7299627e53224566ba1c071f05dca39c
#: b3b86e75ee154a25a39161ec392922fa
msgid "checkmark"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:30
#: 0515ae78f05047279f7026b02ec56896
msgid "Make it easy to discover features and available actions"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:32
#: 354c4800f2094814921b4128e7e769f2
msgid "Provide some understanding of what discovered features do"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:34
#: e2fe80dfa5084954ae4e5bb5cdd5702d
msgid "Offer the ability to easily undo mistakes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:36
#: d402255ad9204c2184847f46e81ced46
msgid "Choose intelligent defaults for settings"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:38
#: 3e9538db6c73414282bd1ce171cd9049
msgid ""
"In making software easy to use, it is crucial to be mindful of `cognitive "
"load <https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cognitive_load>`__ which dictates that "
"*“humans are generally able to hold only seven +/- two units of information "
"in short-term memory.”* Making sure your interfaces don’t pass this short-"
"term memory limit is perhaps the most important factor in helping a user "
"feel comfortable instead of overwhelmed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:43
#: da1634ca245347af821a6ec61d18d9e1
msgid "Easy to Understand"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:45
#: a7c5c4fe602e4ea58322efc3569f7db3
msgid ""
"There will always be the need to communicate things to users. In these "
"cases, an interface should aim to make this information easy to understand. "
"The following are simple guides to help achieve this - none of these are "
"absolute maxims!"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:47
#: ef71ae74195f43208d6519c04fb65068
msgid "|redx| **Avoid Acronyms**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:49
#: 42e20f8b1d084f6eaa64a66bfbebe694
msgid ""
"Acronyms are compact and make good names for command line tools. They do not"
" make graphical user interfaces more intuitive for non-technical users. "
"Until one learns an acronym’s meaning, it is gibberish. Avoid acronyms in "
"your interfaces whenever possible!"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:51
#: 610e2f15e1f740618828ae228e5dfe0a
msgid "``DVM`` - Disposable Virtual Machine"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:53
#: 53c616b526864e1c847808a6549270de
msgid "``GUID`` - Global Unique Identifier"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:55
#: ba6666fdc2b647d896e0ce480e3429cf
msgid "``PID`` - Process Identification Number"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:57
#: b2913f26369d4dddb73aae61168f12b8
msgid "``NetVM`` - Networking Virtual Machine"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:59
#: 4a08dcade1b641bc92e9d0612efef90d
msgid ""
"Despite this rule, some acronyms like ``USB`` are widely used and understood"
" due to being in common use for over a decade. It is good to use these "
"acronyms when the full words like ``Universal Serial Bus`` are more likely "
"to confuse users."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:61
#: 55f79a0a8cca425e89ce91c5108b39b4
msgid "|checkmark| **Use Simple Words**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:63
#: 00b826ebebdb43c7bb09657e11274e43
msgid ""
"Use the minimum amount of words needed to be descriptive, but also "
"informative. Go with common words that are as widely understood. Sometimes, "
"inventing a word such as ``Qube`` to describe a ``virtual machine`` makes "
"the life of the user much easier."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:65
#: 02a3614f155e473ba8755921b1f8f863
msgid ""
"Use ``Disposable Qube`` instead of ``DVM`` or ``Disposable Virtual Machine``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:67
#: 92eee73ca6004cf2bf413e276bca1253
msgid "Use ``interface`` instead of ``GUI`` or ``Graphical User Interface``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:69
#: 700be50aa44f4535bfa8c11776e3000b
msgid ""
"Use ``application number`` instead of ``PID`` or ``Process Identification "
"Number``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:71
#: 0b283cae8ac84232830ce8d7f7169af3
msgid ""
"Use ``Networking`` or ``Networking Qube`` instead of ``NetVM`` given context"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:75
#: 2da7d9e3c79843688e8d44587ae820e7
msgid "|redx| **Avoid Technical Words**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:77
#: 98b9e6db29194443a0958697ad968d68
msgid ""
"Technical words are usually more accurate, but they often *only* make sense "
"to technical users and are confusing and unhelpful to non-technical users. "
"Examples of technical words that might show up in Qubes OS are:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:79
#: bc517672bb0146ad8bad6aee1579c64a
msgid "``root.img``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:81
#: f1252f41153c4e19bfa0d400093c1b11
msgid "``savefile``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:83
#: 3a7166799df842669f328be70a7390aa
msgid "``qrexec-daemon``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:85
#: ae44e5a184e04f279fbfb7af067dc9ab
msgid ""
"These are all terms that have at some point showed up in users’ notification"
" messages. Each term is very specific, but requires the user to understand "
"virtualization to interpret."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:87
#: 12fa86c621944185ab2c748c33679352
msgid "|checkmark| **Use Common Concepts**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:89
#: 553e2860dc9a4166a4439c377bd64e06
msgid ""
"Large amounts of the global population have been using computers for one or "
"two decades and have formed some mental models of how things work. "
"Leveraging these mental models are a huge gain."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:91
#: ed06d08f811b4cc79b3d762ba6028b09
msgid ""
"Use ``disk space`` instead of ``root.img``, since while not quite accurate, "
"it makes contextual sense"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:93
#: e906b333676b41c8bf1d0aea6d0aa955
msgid ""
"Use ``saving`` instead of ``savefile`` as the former is the action trying to"
" be completed"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:95
#: 48f40d8a143d4b0b833b4b9e147d06e9
msgid ""
"Use ``Qubes`` instead of ``qrexec-daemon`` as it gives better context on "
"what is happening"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:97
#: e54368ac98d442e6962272f89a6de60f
msgid ""
"These words are more abstract and user relevant- they help a user understand"
" what is happening based on already known concepts (disk space) or start to "
"form a mental model of something new (Qubes)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:101
#: 5991d2bc6eaa49cab71ea2bdeb551c0b
msgid "|redx| **Avoid Inconsistencies**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:103
#: 62be213bd3ea4fa8b8f5d92607114592
msgid ""
"It is easy to start abbreviating (or making acronyms) of long terms like "
"``Disposable Virtual Machine`` depending on where the term shows up in an "
"interface."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:105
#: 9877ca3ec2324c179193e3a79542f3ac
msgid "``DVM``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:107
#: 8ce18e314d4f4d3e8287c3ee2585fe09
msgid "``DispVM``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:109
#: 4677ba2da8804fc1a8ffa0b1b61e3ecc
msgid "``DisposableVM``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:111
#: e79e3ac83aaa4542b8a73bab53589831
msgid ""
"This variation in terms can cause new users to question or second guess what"
" the three different variations mean, which can lead to inaction or "
"mistakes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:113
#: 0c3b816240354504a8aa271bb159593d
msgid "|checkmark| **Make Things Consistent**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:115
#: 61bf3c389fa24c8bb1b4f0eb9bd5f6c6
msgid ""
"Always strive to keep things consistent in the interfaces as well as "
"documentation and other materials."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:117
#: 70451880deae471f89a39d54622f957e
msgid ""
"Use ``Disposable Qube`` at all times as it meets other criteria as well."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:119
#: dcb23023061c4b63b6de7ce1fc04d67c
msgid ""
"By using the same term throughout an interface, a user can create a mental "
"model and relationship with that term allowing them to feel empowered."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:123
#: cc63c91f9c2940f388d8a15eb8d46ebc
msgid "|redx| **Avoid Duplicate Words**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:125
#: 6ec7cfc8588b4f71b8c597845382fc26
msgid ""
"It is easy to add words like ``Domain`` before items in a list or menu in an"
" attempt to be descriptive, such as:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:134
#: b9271f7c1c6e4a259d1ae9a018a0c240
msgid ""
"The repeated use of the word ``Domain`` requires a user to read it for each "
"item in the list, which makes extra work for the eye in parsing out the "
"relevant word like ``work, banking, or personal``. This also affects "
"horizontal space on fixed width lines."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:136
#: f4a1833c21694f49b2afded7b598b091
msgid "|checkmark| **Create Groups & Categories**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:138
#: 462473eaadfd41b9a397ada442c1cab5
msgid ""
"It is more efficient to group things under headings instead as this allows "
"the eye to easily scan the uniqueness of the items. (As per our previous "
"example:)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:150
#: fd075c9d15f140d1b0188e6de6846663
msgid "Easy To Complete"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:152
#: 0f2e4cb8c44a4f25ad9a4aa1bbf732f1
msgid ""
"Lastly, expected (and unexpected) situations often require user actions or "
"input. Make resolving these occurences as easy as possible to complete the "
"action."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:154
#: e9f026eb6492441c8551af572ac2964a
msgid "|redx| **Don’t Leave Users Stranded**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:156
#: ef573e9a4be04259b9bb1c2fd28a6caf
msgid "Consider the following notifications:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:158
#: 13e64f90bf45439d840b1b0caaab94af
msgid "``The disk space of your Qube \"Work\" is full``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:160
#: 2b6c26f3cfa4443bba15e82254eebb32
msgid "``There was an error saving Qube \"Personal\"``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:162
#: ea4f73005cb94f53ae57ef6d31425ad0
msgid ""
"Instead of displaying solvable errors like these and neglecting to provide a"
" fix:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:164
#: 332bf732d6cb44269779fabf4c89c472
msgid "|checkmark| **Offer Actionable Solutions**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:166
#: 68f793dd42ab44abb62185dcc39dd221
msgid ""
"Error messages and limits such as those in the previous example can be "
"greatly improved by adding buttons or links to helpful information."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:168
#: c4de3258a89d4d6abee94f2c33e9bbd4
msgid "Add a button to ``Increase Disk Space``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:170
#: 11053a89ef354fd1aba5ba0318234eca
msgid "Add a link to a documentation page called ``Troubleshoot saving data``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:172
#: f99c7a2366ae40959cbd9ae5665f25fb
msgid ""
"In adhering to these principles, you’ll make undesirable situations more "
"manageable for users instead of feeling stranded."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:176
#: 56e9baf373ad409fb9dcf95f5b9ed4a9
msgid "|checkmark| **Minimize Repetitive Steps**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:178
#: 8ce8b4472d26447987a4016717046a11
msgid ""
"There are many cases where a user wants to perform an action on more than "
"one file or folder. However in order to do the action, the user must repeat "
"certain steps such as:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:180
#: ../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:198
#: 2d5592aaf96c419caeaf10d7bff29638 a2e0096ae0484d3fbb4ab9a6ca69fc9a
msgid "Click on ``Open File`` from a menu or button"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:182
#: 8e35e706befa422ea31c2e710c5b2ceb
msgid "Navigate through file system"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:184
#: 865b6334b50142ef84d6ec90bf20bd5a
msgid "Click Folder One"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:186
#: a28a7188614d441da45a80524fd2409c
msgid "Click Folder Two"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:188
#: 728599b976e046bd921390a6866f19c0
msgid "Click Folder Three"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:190
#: f633f948161646f4910537e5f5115524
msgid "Click Folder Four"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:192
#: ../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:202
#: 17d8144d72124e4a994bcc24a73fcf19 15844c3cf9844586bb05c1eb217ea889
msgid "Select proper file"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:194
#: f682a7c3f6404047bd46ea999aaf5730
msgid "Complete task on file"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:196
#: 59c94ac88733417189b76dfd02fdecde
msgid ""
"That subtle act of clicking through a file system can prove to be "
"significant if a user needs to open more than a couple files in the same "
"directory. We can alleviate some of the work by changing the process:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:200
#: 0fe693f7a36247f4a382fe79a3e9b9cc
msgid "Remember last open folder/file system"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:204
#: 6358a378ee814664a133807f3fb769bb
msgid "Complete task"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:206
#: ad7283d909ea41e0a073154643fbeca6
msgid ""
"Clearly, cutting out something as simple as navigating through the file "
"system can save a user quite a bit of time. Alternatively, adding a button "
"or menu item like ``Open Multiple Files`` might be even better, because "
"remembering and using relevant hotkeys is often something only power users "
"know how to do!"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:211
#: 557faa7ef4a848ad832bf72a8dba8b04
msgid "GNOME, KDE, and Xfce"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:213
#: c666f19f44064151aa931912d0531c73
msgid ""
"The desktop GUIs that QubesOS versions 1 - 4.1 offer are `KDE "
"<https://kde.org>`__ and `Xfce <https://xfce.org>`__. We are currently "
"migrating towards using `GNOME <https://www.gnome.org>`__. We know some "
"people prefer KDE, but we believe Gnome is easier to use for average non-"
"technical users. Xfce will always be supported, and technical users will "
"always have the choice to use KDE or other desktop environments."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:215
#: 0ade945f42af4a7faa751b0f05d4febb
msgid ""
"This change means you should use `GTK <https://gtk.org/>`__ rather than Qt "
"for new GUIs."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:217
#: 6230890f9988436ba0571c03b01ae236
msgid ""
"All three of these mentioned desktop environments have their own `human "
"interface guidelines "
"<https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Human_interface_guidelines>`__, and we "
"suggest you familiarize yourself with the platform you developing for."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:219
#: b9fccfc4aea64e2aac16afc5a74c254b
msgid ""
"`GNOME Human Interface Guidelines <https://developer.gnome.org/hig/>`__"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:221
#: dca25befc451430dbcc3b56e67214b62
msgid "`KDE HIG <https://hig.kde.org/>`__"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:223
#: 37bad59a5e49493d9c41513b5c7b441c
msgid "`Xfce UI Guidlines <https://wiki.xfce.org/dev/hig/general>`__"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:228
#: c34d21a8ae6d4e5c9dfbb2e9e6c2f278
msgid "Further Learning & Inspiration"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:230
#: 731356b36cf64d09b50b3c236060473c
msgid ""
"Learning to make well designing intuitive interfaces and software is "
"specialized skillset that can take years to cultivate, but if you are "
"interested in furthering your understanding, we suggest the following "
"resources:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:232
#: b0433f24bd8845c5a3beeb4d4268b29b
msgid ""
"`Learn Design Principles "
"<https://web.archive.org/web/20180101172357/http://learndesignprinciples.com/>`__"
" by Melissa Mandelbaum"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:234
#: 8e250293a5614d27b3fc8694057bd465
msgid ""
"`Usability in Free Software <https://jancborchardt.net/usability-in-free-"
"software>`__ by Jan C. Borchardt"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:236
#: ee88249746ca419ea891dd4a2fc2b211
msgid ""
"`Superheroes & Villains in Design <https://vimeo.com/70030549>`__ by Aral "
"Balkan"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:238
#: 958cf992df2a4ab496e14b5384204c2f
msgid ""
"`First Rule of Usability? Don’t Listen to Users "
"<https://www.nngroup.com/articles/first-rule-of-usability-dont-listen-to-"
"users/>`__ by Jakob Nielsen"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:240
#: 020d0530eb494d08bd370ee4bcc8d091
msgid ""
"`10 Usability Heuristics for User Interface Design "
"<https://www.nngroup.com/articles/ten-usability-heuristics/>`__ by Jakob "
"Nielsen"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:242
#: eea3bd55746942b1ba186cc904a9f35a
msgid "`Hack Design <https://hackdesign.org/>`__ - online learning program"
msgstr ""
